## 1.1 Learning Outcome

## 1.2 Getting started

### 1.2.1 Installing and loading the required libraries


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(tidyverse)
```
:::


### 1.2.2 Importing data


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
exam_data <- read_csv("../data/wk1/Exam_data.csv")
```
:::


## 1.3 Introducing ggplot

### 1.3.1 R Graphics VS ggplot


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(exam_data$MATHS)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data, aes(x = MATHS)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=10,
                 boundary = 100,
                 color="black",
                 fill="grey") +
  ggtitle("Distribution of Maths scores")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


