## 1.8 Essential Grammatical Elements in ggplot2: stat

### 1.8.1 Working with stat()


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data,
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-20-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### 1.8.2 Working with stat - the stat_summary() method


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data,
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(geom = "point",
               fun = "mean",
               colour ="red",
               size=4)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-21-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### 1.8.3 Working with stat - the geom() method


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data,
       aes(y = MATHS, x= GENDER)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  geom_point(stat="summary",
             fun="mean",
             colour="red",
             size=4)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-22-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


### 1.8.4 Adding a best fit curve on a scatterplot?


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(data=exam_data,
       aes(x= MATHS, y=ENGLISH)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(size=0.5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](HO_Ex1_submission_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-23-1.png){width=672}
